      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that it can go wrong, but you sounds like you're saying the downsides are way more significant. some people argue that without a strong sense of national identity, you get total social fragmentation and people lose interest in supporting public goods like infrastructure or healthcare because they don't feel connected to their neighbors. isn't nationalism basically the glue that makes a modern state function?",
