      "content": "i hear you on the \"extreme\" part, but it feels like you keep focusing on the worst-case scenarios. when you talk about \"unwelcome extreme forms\" or \"isolating a nation,\" it sounds like you're implying that nationalism is inherently a problem to be managed rather than a positive force. if we're being realistic, isn't the \"global community\" just a vague concept, whereas national identity is what actually provides the legal and social stability people live under? can you just be straight with me—is nationalism fundamentally more of a risk than it is a benefit for a stable society?",
